<taxonomicName id="5212934A240B4BBD6C1E33C7AD06270F" authority="Herbert, 1819" authorityName="Herbert" authorityYear="1819" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Coburgia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Coburgia coccinea" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">Coburgia coccinea</taxonomicName>
(Ruiz &amp; Pav.) Herb., 
<normalizedToken id="B72EE4FC69835FD962974E97F17A5D6B" originalValue="Edwards’">Edwards'</normalizedToken>
Bot. Reg. 28 (Misc.): 54 (1842). (
<figureCitation id="40387F8DA5C621F39A00F8D310BCC31C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. A Plate 28 from Herbert (1837) with Stenomesson rubrum Herb. illustrated (number 6, red arrow). Stenomesson breviflorum Herb. is illustrated in the same plate (numbers 7 &amp; 8, black arrows), evidence that Herbert considered these two different species B Painting of Coburgia coccinea Herb. [= Clinanthus ruber (Herb.) Meerow &amp; A. Cano] that accompanied the description by Herbert (1841) C Clinanthus ruber, photographed in Peru. Photo by Oscar de Viveroscar D Clinanthus coccineus (Ruiz &amp; Pav.) Meerow, loma form, photographed in Lima Dept., Peru. Photo by Norton Cuba Melly." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/340296" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4B, D</figureCitation>
